name: PrismAnalytics-Tables-GET-GetTables
description: [Prism Analytics] GET /tables — Get tables that the current user has permission on

schema.name: limit
schema.description:
The maximum number of object data entries included in the response.
- default: 20
- max: 100

schema.name: name
schema.description: The API name of the table to retrieve a single table.

schema.name: offset
schema.description:
The offset to the first object in a collection to include in the response.
default: 0

schema.name: type
schema.description:
How much information to be returned in response JSON.
The value for type dictates the response fields that are excluded.
- default: summary
- full : Returns tableResponse, excluding user permissions
- permissions : Returns tableResponse with user permissions. Schema fields are excluded
- summary : Returns summarized tableResponse, excluding schema fields and user permissions
Note: The HTTP 200 response below is for type "full"

schema.name: type
schema.description:
How much information to be returned in response JSON.
The value for type dictates the response fields that are excluded.
- default: full
- full : Returns tableResponse, excluding user permissions
- permissions : Returns tableResponse with user permissions. Schema fields are excluded
- summary : Returns summarized tableResponse, excluding schema fields and user permissions
Note: The HTTP 200 response below is for "type" full

name: PrismAnalytics-DataChanges-GET-GetDataChanges
description: [Prism Analytics] GET /dataChanges — Get data changes accessible by a user

schema.name: limit
schema.description:
The maximum number of object data entries to be included in the response.
- default: 20
- max: 500

schema.name: name
schema.description:
The name of a data change.

Note: Either "type" or "name" query parameter must be set in order to receive the response as object "dataChangeResponseList" below.
- default: -- (empty)

schema.name: offset
schema.description:
The offset to the first object in a collection to include in the response.
default: 0

schema.name: type
schema.description:
How much data change information to be returned. Note: The model response for HTTP 200 below is for type "summary"

Note: Either "type" or "name" query parameter needs to be set in order to receive the HTTP 200 response below.
- default: -- (empty)
- full: Every element in type "summary", plus description, application, categories, tags, mappings
- summary: Returns summarized data change details specified in the model "dataChangeSummary"
